<br>
I'm an aussie in a US guild. USA 9pm is ~9am for me and I have a full time job thats 9am to 5pm (In theory anyway..).<br>
Making it to raids Pre-pop was hard but not impossible.<br>
Many of the important non-pop raids are on rotation and semi planable (esp NToV).  I could book days off or occasionally ring up and say I would be in late (I'm on flexi time, I never threw a sicky tho).<br>
With PoP this all changed. None of the flag mob are on a rotation. The guild did flag mobs as they poped and almost always on a week day. Whats more the guild only wanted to do the major flag mobs two or three times. It took me months to get Grummus, AD etc and I still don't have TT. Every one of those flags was a pain to get. Slowly but surely I fell further and further behind. In the end I gave up, the guild stopped doing TT,the HoHb trials and Caprin etc, I also stopped playing altogether for over three months and have recently started playing infrequently for xp only.<br>
Other than being able to see a tanglable advancement while xping (ie play for 3-4hr get an aa ), Pop has been a very bad expansion for me. Planer flags killed it for me.<br>
<br>
Now that they are giving away all the flagged zones I worked to get into I'm going to find the few solo xp spots I have crowded out. RE:Groups Yes I love grouping. But at 8am usa time nobody is on (eg /who enchanter 60 65 gives 3 of which 2 are in the bazaar and the other is afk and the lfg tool finds a war, a rogue and a bard who have been lfg for the last hour). I do get groups around 10am (10pm for me) but thats hours of wasted time before 10 if I can not solo.<br>
Letting in the lower level players will just mean more disfunctional groups. A lot of the early morning groups have problems with their group make up.<br>
<br>
